translated:
Ingemarsson, Ernst Gunnar Oskar was a county treasurer from Växjö. He was born on July 2nd, 1894 in As, Jönköping. His parents were a primary school teacher and a cantor, A. J. L and Emma Jonasson. He married Karin Weidenhaijn in 1931 and they had four children: Ingmari (born 1932), Sverker (born 1935), Anders (born 1941), and Karin (born 1944). 

He obtained his high school diploma in Växjö in 1913 and graduated with a law degree from Lund University in 1917. He served as a temporary judge in the Lysing and Göstring districts, as well as a mayor in Söderköping. He was a county accountant in Östergötland from 1921 to 1925, then a permanent county bookkeeper there. In 1928, he became a county assessor in Väster-Norrland County. He was appointed county treasurer in that same county in 1934, then transferred to Kronoberg County in 1943, where he held the same position until the end of his career. He also received the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO).
